The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Jan. 24: The cabinet today app-roved a plan to split the state electricity board. 

 The bifurcation was necessary to conform to the Electricity Act, 2003. Power minister Mrinal Banerjee said Bengal became the 16th state to restructure its power utility in tune with the new act. The move will improve commercial efficiency and customer service, he added. Two companies the West Bengal State Electricity Transmission Company Ltd and the West Bengal State Electricity Distribution Company Ltd would come into existence on April 1.

 Calcutta: Cognizant, Tech Mahindra and HCL have booked space at the 48-acre IT park promoted by the ML Dalmiya Group at Bantala. Jag- mohan Dalmiya and the IT minister discussed land allotment with industries minister Nirupam Sen on Wednesday.

 Midnapore: The Nandigram Youth Congress chief has been arrested. He told police they would be beaten up if they tried to enter his village. 

 Midnapore: Police detained an eight-year-old boy at Mecheda station on Wednesday. He fled home, in Bihar, after a tiff with his mother.




